<h1>Stream link identifier</h1>

<p>
This tool can be used to assign each link in a stream network a unique numeric identifier. This grid is used by a number of other stream network analysis tools. The user must specify the names of a streams raster image and D8 pointer image. The streams file is used to designate which grid cells contain a stream and the pointer image is used to traverse the stream network. Stream cells are designated in the streams image as all values greater than zero. Thus all non-stream or background grid cells are commonly assigned either zeros or <b><i>NoData</b></i> values. Background cells will be assigned the <b><i>NoData</b></i> value in the output image. The output raster is of an <i>integer</i> data type and <i>categorical</i> data scale. The pointer image should be created using the <a href="FlowPointerD8.html">D8 algorithm</a>.</p>


